    <p>In Global Navigation, click the <strong>Inbox</strong> link.</p>
  </div>
</div>
 
  </div>

      <div class="step screensteps-section screensteps-depth-1" id="view_unread_message" data-step-uuid="22e2c90a-251b-475c-91d7-67b17a5c0d24">
    <h2 id="view_unread_message" class="step-title screensteps-heading">View Unread Message</h2>
        <div class="image screensteps-image">
      <img src="https://media.screensteps.com/image_assets/assets/007/633/251/original/0f9d328f-9e5b-4649-bdd0-08bfb36c8189.png" srcset="" alt="View Unread Message" height="457" width="418">
  </div>
 
      <div class="step-instructions screensteps-textblock">
  <div id="text-content_6F485A90-1EEE-0135-4E5F-22000AB760A3" class="text-block-content">
    <p>All unread messages have an indicator next to the message. Once a conversation has been read, the blue dot changes to a gray circle.</p>
  </div>
</div>
 
  </div>

      <div class="step screensteps-section screensteps-depth-1" id="mark_as_unread" data-step-uuid="49452d44-8611-4f0a-9e70-ab7c54acca5d">
    <h2 id="mark_as_unread" class="step-title screensteps-heading">Mark as Unread</h2>
        <div class="image screensteps-image">
      <img src="https://media.screensteps.com/image_assets/assets/007/633/253/original/5a5b5834-fe55-4a20-a8f2-9f8a84a5241d.png" srcset="" alt="Mark as Unread" height="285" width="426">
  </div>
 
      <div class="step-instructions screensteps-textblock">
  <div id="text-content_6F488E40-1EEE-0135-4E61-22000AB760A3" class="text-block-content">
    <p>If you want to mark a conversation as unread, click the read indicator [1]. The message will now show the unread indicator [2].</p>
  </div>
</div>
 
        <div class="step screensteps-section screensteps-depth-2" id="mark_multiple_messages" data-step-uuid="026a65ad-3dba-4049-8065-44a70137cbfd">
    <h3 id="mark_multiple_messages" class="step-title screensteps-heading">Mark Multiple Messages</h3>
        <div class="image screensteps-image">
      <a href="https://media.screensteps.com/image_assets/assets/007/633/256/original/7d6cc405-da5d-49ba-95ef-c4ce1b3cfa9e.png" class="screensteps-image-zoom" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer">
        <img src="https://media.screensteps.com/image_assets/assets/007/633/256/medium/7d6cc405-da5d-49ba-95ef-c4ce1b3cfa9e.png" srcset="" alt="Mark Multiple Messages" height="738" width="855">
      </a>
  </div>
 
      <div class="step-instructions screensteps-textblock">
  <div id="text-content_6F48C270-1EEE-0135-4E63-22000AB760A3" class="text-block-content">
    <p>You can mark multiple conversations as unread or read by pressing the command key (Mac) or the control key (Windows) while clicking multiple messages, or by selecting the message checkbox [1].</p>
<p>Locate and click the settings icon and choose <strong>Mark all as unread</strong> link [2].  </p>
<p>If you select multiple unread messages, you will see <strong>Mark all as read </strong>link [3].</p>
  </div>
</div>
 
  </div>
 
  </div>

